            "text": "ROOT",
            "relation": "null"
        },
        {
            "id": 1,
            "parent": 15,
            "text": "The treatment of surgical patients",
            "relation": "BACKGROUND"
        },
        {
            "id": 2,
            "parent": 1,
            "text": "who are confirmed or suspected of coronavirus disease 2019 ( COVID-19 )",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 3,
            "parent": 1,
            "text": "is a challenge for all anesthesiologists . <S>",
            "relation": "SAME-UNIT"
        },
        {
            "id": 4,
            "parent": 1,
            "text": "The safety of both patients and healthcare workers should be taken into consideration",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 5,
            "parent": 4,
            "text": "when performing anesthesia management for patients with COVID-19 . <S>",
            "relation": "TEMPORAL"
        },
        {
            "id": 6,
            "parent": 4,
            "text": "General anesthesia",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 7,
            "parent": 6,
            "text": "requiring airway intervention",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 8,
            "parent": 6,
            "text": "may exacerbate COVID-19 pneumonia ,",
            "relation": "SAME-UNIT"
        },
        {
            "id": 9,
            "parent": 8,
            "text": "and aerosol generation during airway intervention risks COVID-19 transmission to medical staff . <S>",
            "relation": "JOINT"
        },
        {
            "id": 10,
            "parent": 6,
            "text": "However , regional anesthesia is not an aerosol - generating procedure . <S>",
            "relation": "COMPARISON"
        },
        {
            "id": 11,
            "parent": 10,
            "text": "The neuraxial anesthesia may have little adverse influence on clinical outcomes in patients with COVID-19",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 12,
            "parent": 11,
            "text": "after reviewing previous case reports . <S>",
            "relation": "CAUSE-RESULT"
        },
        {
            "id": 13,
            "parent": 11,
            "text": "Regional anesthesia may have some advantages over general anesthesia for this group of patients ,",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 14,
            "parent": 13,
            "text": "but unplanned conversion to general anesthesia during surgery is not preferred . <S>",
            "relation": "COMPARISON"
        },
        {
            "id": 15,
            "parent": 0,
            "text": "Thus , careful consideration should be given",
            "relation": "ROOT"
        },
        {
            "id": 16,
            "parent": 17,
            "text": "to ensure",
            "relation": "ATTRIBUTION"
        },
        {
            "id": 17,
            "parent": 15,
            "text": "that the surgery is performed entirely under regional anesthesia . <S>",
            "relation": "ENABLEMENT"
        },
        {
            "id": 18,
            "parent": 15,
            "text": "The use of ultrasound guidance and the performance by an experienced physician may reduce the incidence of failed block and complications . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 19,
            "parent": 18,
            "text": "The use of long - acting local anesthetic prolongs the anesthetic effect of regional anesthesia . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 20,
            "parent": 19,
            "text": "Besides , a safe and sufficient dose of local anesthetic should be used . <S> <P>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        }
    ]
}